nd use this result to prove that both $R^{(p)}$ and $B^{(p)}$ are\ncertain non-principal W-algebras of type $A$ at boundary admissible levels. The\nsame uniqueness result also shows that $R^{(p)}$ and $B^{(p)}$ are the chiral\nalgebras of Argyres-Douglas theories of type $(A_1, D_{2p})$ and $(A_1,\nA_{2p-3})$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jan 2020 15:05:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-23"}
